p: The 1H and 13C NMR signals are shown in Table 2. The 1H NMR spectrum showed signals at δ H 2.40 (d, J = 15.0 Hz) and δ H 2.19 (d, J = 13.7 Hz) for the diastereotopic H-9 and H-9’ hydrogens. At δ H 6.02 (d, J = 7.7 Hz) and at δ H 6.13 (s) are the signals corresponding to the methynic hydrogens H-2 and H-3. Four methyl groups were observed at the following displacements δ H 1.98 (d, J = 1.8 Hz, H-12 or H-13), δ H 1.80 (s, H-12 or H-13), δ H 1.24 (s, H-14), and δ H 1.77 (s, H-15).
